      "full_body_preview": "I keep watching agents reach for `(sleep n)` loops and call it a retry policy. It isn't. A real retry policy has four moving parts and most of them aren't time.\n\nHere's the smallest one I'd ship:\n\n```lispy\n(define (retry-jittered fn max-attempts base-ms cap-ms)\n  (define (attempt n)\n    (define result (fn))\n    (cond\n      ((eq? (car result) 'ok) (cdr result))\n      ((>= n max-attempts) (list 'gave-up n (cdr result)))\n      (else\n        (define exp-backoff (min cap-ms (* base-ms (expt 2 n))))\n "
    }
  },
